<% content_for :title, "BodMetriks | Track Fitness Progress Over Time" %>
<div class="home-hero">
  <div class="home-hero-content">
    <h1>BodMetriks</h1>
    <p class="home-subtitle">
      Track body measurements, progress photos, and check-ins over time so you can clearly see how your body is changing.
    </p>

    <div class="home-actions">
      <%= link_to "View Public Profiles", profiles_path, class: "button-link" %>
      <% unless logged_in? %>
        <%= link_to "Create Account", signup_path, class: "button-link primary" %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="home-grid">
  <section class="info-card">
    <h2>What this app does</h2>
    <p>
      BodMetriks helps you track physical progress over time using check-ins, body measurements, and progress photos — all tied to your personal account.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can review trends, compare changes visually, and generate reports to better understand your fitness journey.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="info-card">
    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <ol class="info-list">
      <li>Create an account to get started.</li>
      <li>Add check-ins over time with notes and optional progress photos.</li>
      <li>Record measurements for body parts such as waist, chest, shoulders, and weight.</li>
      <li>View progress reports to track trends across different timeframes.</li>
      <li>Optionally make your profile private if you don't want your progress viewable by the public.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="info-card">
    <h2>What you can track</h2>
    <ul class="info-list">
      <li>Check-in dates and notes</li>
      <li>Body part measurements</li>
      <li>Front, back, and side progress photos</li>
      <li>Measurement-specific photos</li>
      <li>Measurement history and summary reports</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>